Package: MCPModX
Type: Package
Title: MCP-Mod with Model-Assisted Covariate Adjustment under Missing Outcomes
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Cheng-Han", "Yang", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "bingo82728@gmail.com"),
    person("Ruitao", "Lin", role = "aut", email = "rlin@mdanderson.org"))
Description: An extension of the Multiple Comparison Procedure and Modelling
    (MCP-Mod) methodology for dose-finding that performs model-assisted
    covariate adjustment and accommodates missing outcomes that are missing at
    random. Marginal arm means are estimated by inverse-probability-weighted
    g-computation / augmented inverse-probability weighting (AIPW); inference
    uses the stacked M-estimation (sandwich) covariance that accounts for
    estimation of the observation- and outcome-model nuisance parameters
    (Theorem 3.3). Supports the optimal-contrast MCP testing step with a
    multiplicity-adjusted critical value and the generalised-AIC model-averaging
    Mod step. Continuous (identity link) and binary (logit link) outcomes are
    supported; for binary outcomes the target estimand is the marginal
    placebo-adjusted log-odds dose-response curve.
